==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heeltap
<hw>Heel"tap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of
the segments of leather in the heel of a shoe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small portion of liquor left in a glass after
drinking.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bumpers around and no <xex>heeltaps</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sheridan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heeltap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Heeltap
<hw>Heel"tap`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Heeltapped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Heeltapping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To add a piece of leather to
the heel of (a shoe, boot, etc.)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heeltool</ent>⟦br⟧
